        <briefdescription>
<para>Registers a new system of type T. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Creates a <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1TypedSystem" kindref="compound">TypedSystem&lt;T&gt;</ref> wrapper, stores it in the registry indexed by <ref refid="classhelios_1_1engine_1_1core_1_1data_1_1SystemTypeId" kindref="compound">SystemTypeId</ref>, and returns a reference to the underlying T instance.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>T</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The concrete system type. Must satisfy <ref refid="concepthelios_1_1engine_1_1runtime_1_1world_1_1HasUpdate" kindref="compound">HasUpdate</ref>. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Args</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Constructor argument types for T.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>args</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Arguments forwarded to the T constructor.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>Reference to the registered system instance.</para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="pre"><para>No system of type T is already registered. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>SystemsView returns systems in the order they were registered. The game loop guarantees this: calling addSystem() on a pass preserves deterministic execution by maintaining the insertion order. Once removeSystem() is implemented, updating systemsView_ must be reviewed.</para>
